Sampson Itode, Port Harcourt The Rivers State Governor, Nyesom Wike, has ordered the Federal Road Safety Corps in the state to arrest and prosecute any tricycle riders popularly known as Keke Napep caught plying major roads in the state. Wike stated this in Port Harcourt on Friday during the inauguration of the 2020 ember months safety campaign of the FRSC. The governor who was represented by the state Commissioner for Transportation, Osima Gina, said for the protection of lives on the highways, tricycle riders were barred from operating on all major roads in the state. He said, â€œAny Keke rider you catch on any of the major roads please apprehend and detain them. Let the leaders of Keke riders know that it is not only the taskforce that will be set up by the state government, but as partners in the business of saving lives on the road, the Federal Road Safety Corps will not allow Keke to ply the major roads. Copyright PUNCH.
